§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬linear functional❭ on a vector space $V$ with field $k$
    is a function $f: V → k$ which satisfies
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(λ x + μ y) = λ f(x) + μ f(y) ⦉
    ⦉
    for all $\lambda, \mu \in k$ and $x, y ∈ V$. ⦉
⦉

§§ Examples ⦉
𝍫 ⦊
  ‣ Define $F: 𝗖^n \to 𝗖$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ F(x_1, …, x_n) = c_1x_1 + c_2x_2 + ⋯ + c_nx_n ⦉
    ⦉
    where $c_1, …, c_n ∈ 𝗖$. ⦉

  ‣ Let $(c_n)_{n \in \N} \in \ell^{\infty}$. Define $F_c: \ell^1
    \to \C$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ F_c((x_n)_{n \in \N}) = \sum_{n = 1}^{\infty} c_n x_n. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

